article.headline: Md.-Eastern Shore 88, Shenandoah 64
article.story: PRINCESS ANNE, Md. (AP) -- Corey Brown scored a game-high 30 points, shot 11-for-16 from the field and grabbed four rebounds, and Maryland-Eastern Shore defeated Shenandoah 88-64 Wednesday night. UMES led from the beginning, taking a 12-point lead at 15-3 on a three-pointer by Brown at 13:46. UMES' lead never fell below double digits afterward. Ed Tyson contributed 21 points for UMES (3-14). Antonio McMillion grabbed a team-high eight rebounds. Jeremiah Lawrence scored a team-high 24 points and grabbed a game-high 11 rebounds for Shenandoah (6-8). Mouktar Fawehinmi contributed 16 points and 10 rebounds.
